        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 5:17AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 517 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Albany, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mccarty Lake, Us-183 Near The Throckmorton-
Baylor County Line, Lusk, Throckmorton, The Intersection Of Us-
283 And Ranch Road 209, Moran, Us-180 Near The Shackelford-
Stephens County Line, Ibex, The Intersection Of Us-183 And Us-
283, Elbert, Woodson, The Intersection Of Us-
380 And Highway 222, Fort Griffin, and Albany.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
